Italy's public debt rises to record levels
Italy's public debt in June 2016 exceeded 2,248 trillion euros.
The central bank of the country said that this amount is a historical maximum, reports RIA Novosti.
The previous record was set in May of this year.
Then the size of the public debt reached 2,228 trillion euros.
It is noted that for the first half of the year, Italy’s debt burden increased by 77.2 billion euros.
Earlier it was reported that at the end of 2015, Italy’s national debt was 132.7% of the country’s GDP.
Meanwhile, the Italian Minister of Economy and Finance, Pierre Carlo Padoan, predicted a decline in this indicator in 2016 to 130.9 percent, and in 2018 to 123.4 percent of GDP.
Payments from the airport received 141 victims of the terrorist attack in "Domodedovo".
141 people received charitable payments from the fund "Aviation", which was created by the management of the airport "Domodedovo" to help the victims of the terrorist attack in 2011, reports Interfax.
According to airport spokesman Alexander Vlasov, two more applications are currently under consideration.
"Charity payments to the victims of the 2011 terrorist attack continue from the fund and comprehensive assistance is provided to resolve existing issues," Vlasov added, recalling that the fund's website containing full information on the procedure for providing charitable assistance was created specifically to facilitate interaction with the victims.
In 2011, in the arrival hall of foreign airlines Domodedovo, a suicide bomber fired an explosive device.
The attack killed 37 people and injured 172 others.
Scientists have found an animal that can live for 500 years
An international group of biologists has come to the conclusion that the longest-lived vertebrate animal is the Greenland polar shark, which can live for about 500 years.
Scientists conducted a radiocarbon analysis of the lens of the eye of 28 Greenland sharks.
The largest shark, which is more than five meters long, can be between 272 and 512 years old.
Biologists believe that a low metabolism plays an important role in shark longevity, which leads to slow development.
Female Greenland sharks only reach sexual maturity by the age of 150.
Previously, it was believed that the longest life of all vertebrate animals lives "neighbor" of the shark - Greenland whale.
The oldest specimen known to scientists was just over 210 years old.
