Prolong the fruiting.
What can we do to keep the harvest going until the end of the season?
Tells Yulia Belopukhova, agronomist and daughter-in-law.
It is time for tall tomatoes to arrange a haircut: remove new stepchildren, cut the tops, remove all the leaves until the penultimate brush with fruits and inflorescences with small ovaries - they will not have time to ripen.
All tomatoes, regardless of the "constitution", as well as peppers and eggplants, are fed with ash-superphosphate extract, treated with biopreparations (ripener - to accelerate the flow and growth of fruits, Fitosporin-M, Fitolavin, Gamair, Bactofit - from diseases, immunocytophyte, immunocytophyte, immunophyte).
Of the chemicals at the end of summer, it is worth using only copper sulfate, colloidal sulfur and green soap.
We do the last watering of the plants.
Long-breasted cucumbers in the greenhouse are lowered from the wallpaper so that the lower, bare part of the stem (25-40 cm) lies on the ground, watered with warm water and a solution of Zircon, sprinkle the stem with 5-7 cm of compost.
To prolong the fruiting of zucchini is also easy: cut the old leaves, pour warm water and a solution of complex fertilizer, pour fertile soil under the bush.
To protect against the night cold, install arcs with a covering material over the bed.
Keep the plants open during the day and close after sunset.
Signs of the end.
What shows that Russia is coming out of the crisis?
Economists have seen signs of Russia’s exit from the longest recession in 20 years.
According to analysts polled by Bloomberg, the GDP of the Russian Federation shows a positive dynamics - in the second quarter of GDP decreased by 0.8% in annual terms.
This figure is the lowest since the beginning of 2015.
According to the latest Rosstat data, the recession of the Russian economy in the second quarter slowed to 0.6%.
The stabilization of the situation was also recently announced by the Central Bank and the Ministry of Economic Development.
There is slow growth ahead.
According to CBR experts, the recession in the Russian economy is a thing of the past.
“The index estimate of Russia’s GDP indicates that the recession is behind and slow economic growth is ahead,” the Bank of Russia’s Bulletin “What Trends Are Saying” reads.
The regulator’s modular estimate of GDP for the current quarter was increased to 0.4%, the estimate for the fourth quarter is 0.5%.
According to the representative of the Ministry of economic development, during the second quarter, the decline in Russian GDP stopped in the second quarter, amounting to 0.2%.
In the second quarter, the seasonally adjusted GDP decline was 0.2% compared to the previous quarter.
But during the quarter the decline stopped: in April it amounted to 0.2%, and in May and June the change in GDP was in the range of 0-0.15”, – quotes the representative of the MAYOR of RIA Novosti.
The slowdown in the Russian economy over the past five quarters indicates that “the bottom has been passed”.
Among other markers pointing to signs of a revival of the national economy, Bloomberg calls the growth of demand for electricity and rail transportation, the revival of business.
Adjusting to the fact that the year is leap year, it is clear that the dynamics of plus 1% of electricity consumption can be half due to an additional working day.
Add to this the lower annual average temperature in the first quarter.
The next argument is the growth of freight traffic, but it is difficult to obtain accurate data here, and plus or minus 0.5% of the half-yearly volume can also be explained by seasonality, "explains Kirill Yakovenko from ALOR BROKER.
However, there are other, more obvious signs of the stabilization of the Russian economy.
For example, reducing price pressure.
In July, the consumer price index was 7.2% compared to 15.6% in the same month last year.
Moreover, Rosstat has been recording deflation for the last two weeks.
Prices in Russia fell for the first time in five years.
If you look at the dynamics of the ruble exchange rate, which, although it showed strong fluctuations at the beginning of the year, at the end of August since the beginning of the year strengthened by 12%.
This is also one of the signs of recovery, which should be followed by indicators from the real sector of the economy," Yakovenko stressed.
In addition, since April in the Russian Federation there is an increase in industrial production.
In June, the figure increased by 1.7%.
The rate of decline in foreign trade turnover is slowing from -32.8% in January 2016 to -20.7% in May.
Positive dynamics is also demonstrated by the situation in the labor market, where the unemployment rate fell to 5.4%.
It was lower only in September 2015 (5.2%).
Despite the prosperous situation on the labor market, the issue of real disposable incomes of the population is left to be desired.
In annual terms, the figure decreases by 4.8%.
This factor can hamper economic recovery, as household spending contributes significantly to GDP.
As a rule, their share in the structure of the economy exceeds 50%.
In addition to low consumer activity, as risk factors for economic growth can also be called rigid policy of the Bank of Russia.
The regulator keeps the rate at 10.5%, which is not the best effect on the real sector.
A negative factor is the insufficiently high level of investment, which hinders the development of industrial potential.
But in general, it can be assumed that by the end of the year the rate of decline of the Russian economy will slow down to -0.5% against -3.7% in 2015", - says analyst of GC Forex Club Irina Rogova.
