Head of the Presidential Administration of the Russian Federation Anton Vaino.
On Friday, August 12, Vladimir Putin appointed Anton Vaino head of the administration of the President of Russia.
Previously, this position was held by Sergei Ivanov.
"The head of state by his decree appointed Anton Vaino Head of the administration of the President of the Russian Federation, dismissing him from his post," the decree, signed by Putin and published on the Kremlin's website, said.
Since May 2012, Vaino was the deputy head of the presidential administration of the Russian Federation.
Anton Eduardovich Vaino was born on February 17, 1972 in Tallinn.
The father is Eduard Vaino, Chairman of the Cuba-Russia Business Council at the Chamber of Commerce and Industry of the Russian Federation and Vice President for External Relations and Interaction with Shareholders of AvtoVAZ.
Grandfather - Karl Vaino - from 1978 to 1988, the first secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Estonia.
In 1996 he graduated from the Moscow State Institute of International Relations of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Russia, Faculty of International Relations.
From 1996 to 2001, he worked at the Russian Embassy in Japan, then in the Second Department of Asia of the Russian Foreign Ministry.
From 2002 to 2004, he held various positions in the Office of the Protocol of the President of the Russian Federation.
From 2004 to 2007 - Deputy Head of the Protocol and Organizational Department of the President of the Russian Federation.
From 2007 to 2007, he was the first deputy head of the protocol of the President of the Russian Federation.
From October 2007 to April 2008 - Deputy Head of the Cabinet of the Government of the Russian Federation.
On April 25, 2008, he was appointed head of protocol of the Prime Minister of the Russian Federation, deputy head of the Cabinet of the Government of the Russian Federation.
Since December 27, 2011 - Minister of the Russian Federation - Head of the Government of the Russian Federation.
On May 22, 2012, he was appointed Deputy Head of the Presidential Administration of the Russian Federation.
He is fluent in English and Japanese.
Current State Counselor of the Russian Federation 1st class (class rank assigned by the Decree of the President of the Russian Federation of January 22, 2008)
Diploma of Honor of the President of the Russian Federation (16 February 2012) for merits in ensuring the activities of the Government of the Russian Federation and many years of conscientious work.
Gratitude of the President of the Russian Federation (24 November 2005) for the merits in the preparation and holding of solemn events dedicated to the 60th anniversary of the Victory in the Great Patriotic War.
