Moscow "Gazstroybank" was left without a license of the Central Bank.
On Friday, August 12, 2016, the Central Bank of Russia revoked the license to conduct banking operations from the credit institution Joint Stock Commercial Bank "GAZSTROYBANK", registered in Moscow.
According to the regulator, JSC JSC "GASTROYBANK" carried out a high-risk credit policy related to the placement of funds in low-quality assets.
An adequate assessment of the risks taken at the request of the supervisory authority and a reliable reflection of the value of the bank's assets have led to the emergence of grounds for the credit institution to implement measures to prevent bankruptcy.
In addition, the credit institution was involved in questionable transit operations.
The bank has appointed a temporary administration for the period of validity until the appointment of a competitive manager or liquidator.
The powers of the executive bodies of the credit institution are suspended in accordance with federal laws.
JSC "GAZSTROYBANK" is a participant of the deposit insurance system.
Recall that the payment of insurance compensation to bank depositors, including individual entrepreneurs, in accordance with the Federal Law No. 177-FZ "On Insurance of Deposits of Individuals in Banks of the Russian Federation" is provided in the amount of 100% of the balance of funds, but not more than 1.4 million rubles in total per depositor.
Payments, according to the Deposit Insurance Agency, will begin no later than August 26, 2016.
According to the report, the amount of assets of JSC JSC JSC "GASTROYBANK" on August 1, 2016 took 335 place in the banking system of the Russian Federation.
