WSJ: The United States is considering imposing sanctions against Russia because of the hacking of the servers of the Democrats.
U.S. officials are considering introducing new sanctions against Russia in response to the hacking of the Democratic Party’s servers, writes The Wall Street Journal, citing sources.
To impose sanctions, the administration of US President Barack Obama will have to formally accuse Russia of attacking servers or Russian-backed hackers.
