FAS fined Google almost half a billion rubles
The reason was the distortion of competition in the market of mobile applications.
Antitrust proceedings were initiated at the initiative of Yandex.
The Russian company claimed that Google provides smartphone manufacturers with access to Android components on terms that prohibited the pre-installation of applications from other developers, in particular, from Yandex.
The FAS found confirmation of these claims and established that the company abused its dominant position in the market and imposed on mobile device manufacturers the installation along with the Google Play Store of other applications.
According to the results of the inspection, the Federal Antimonopoly Service decided to punish Google, Deputy Head of the FAS Alexey Dotsenko said.
The fine must be paid within 60 days of the entry into force of the decree.
The FAS concluded that all companies, including transnational corporations, must comply with the law on protection of competition.
In turn, Google intends to first examine the decision and only then determine the next steps: to implement it or to challenge it.
The Federal Antimonopoly Service recognized the company as a violation of competition law in September last year and ordered to adjust the contracts until December 18.
However, Google has not given its consent.
Since then, the company and the department have been conducting legal proceedings.
The FAS noted that, despite the fine, they are discussing with Google the possibility of concluding a settlement agreement.
This measure will lead to nothing.
This opinion "Echo of Moscow" was expressed by the leading analyst of Mobile research group Eldar Murtazin.
Murtazin also noted that the fine will not affect users or the competitiveness of the corporation.
