Bulgaria shows inflation for the first time in 8 months
Inflation in Bulgaria was 1% per month in July, according to national statistics.
This is the highest figure in years (since June 2012) and the first higher than zero since October last year, when a positive 0.2% was shown.
The average annual inflation measured by the CPI for the last 12 months (August 2015 - July 2016) compared to the previous 12 months (August 2014 - July 2015) was -0.8%.
The consumer price index in July 2016 compared to June 2016 was 101.0 %, i.e. monthly inflation was 1.0 %.
The inflation indicator since the beginning of the year (July 2016 compared to December 2015) amounted to -0.2%, and the annual inflation in July 2016 compared to July 2015 amounted to -0.2%.
In July 2016, compared to the previous month, there was an increase in the price of the following consumer goods: food and non-alcoholic beverages (1.7%); transport (1.8%); recreation and culture (6.3%); restaurants and hotels (1.2%); other goods and services (0.3%).
Prices decreased for clothing and footwear (2.2%); furniture, household appliances and regular maintenance (0.5%); health (0.1%).
Prices remained at the same level as in the previous month for alcoholic beverages and tobacco; housing, water, electricity, gas and other fuels; communication systems; and education.
