So when some users were offered a lens this week that endowed them with slanted eyes, crooked teeth and swollen cheeks, some critics saw it as a racist caricature of Asians.
And they wondered if these recurring contradictions pointed to the company’s more serious diversity-related problem.
Messages spread on Wednesday followed by outrage in reports on The Verge and Motherboard, a day after Snapchat said it had removed the feature.
The company commented: the lens was conceived as a tribute to the characters of the anime, not as a caricature of Asians.
But to experts who know about racism, the lens reminded offensive stereotypes in action.
Others completely rejected the comparison with the anime.
