Military leadership distorted intelligence about ISIS, says the committee of Congress
U.S. Central Command officials have altered intelligence reports to provide a more optimistic picture of the war against Islamic State in Iraq and Syria than the events on the ground warrant, a congressional commission said in a report released Thursday.
