The procedure, Schiff said, “stopped the release of intelligence documents,” damaged the morale of analysts and “insufficiently reflects divergent views.”
But Schiff and the Democrats say they found no evidence that the White House was trying to force CENTCOM analysts to tailor their findings to “a given or political interpretation.”
The preliminary results of the congressional investigation were presented on Tuesday by the portal The Daily Beast.
