Critics of Trump, including 2012 Republican presidential candidate Mitt Romney and other fellow Republicans, said his refusal raised questions about his condition, his charitable contributions, his business operations and other ties, including with Russia.
Clinton grabbed onto the issue and released an online video on Friday highlighting prominent Republicans who persuaded Trump to release his tax returns.
On Thursday, she raised the issue during a speech on the economy in Michigan.
“He refuses to do what every presidential candidate has done for decades without exception: publish his tax returns,” she said.
