Notifications on transport tax will stop sending by mail - site Behind the wheel www.zr.ru
The Tax Inspectorate changed the procedure for sending notices on property taxes.
All Russian car owners are accustomed to the unchanged scheme over the years: in summer and autumn, they receive receipts by mail for the payment of transport tax for the previous year.
However, this year many of them will not wait.
The fact is that the tax inspectorate changed the procedure for notifying citizens without unnecessary noise.
Those who are registered in the "Personal account of the taxpayer" on the official website of the office narodn.ru, notifications will come in electronic form.
The inspection automatically considered such Russians as online users and deleted them from the standard, "paper" mailing list.
The innovation will affect all owners of vehicles and real estate.
Everyone else will continue to receive the usual letters.
However, the possibility of returning to the old scheme is also available to account holders on the site.
To do this, they will have to visit the tax office during August and write a statement.
On the one hand, the new order is more modern and convenient.
The notification will appear in the "personal account" immediately after compilation, while the letter will last several days and may be lost altogether.
In addition, the number of users of the Internet service of the tax inspectorate exceeded 18 million people, which will allow the department to seriously save on mailing.
On the other hand, the modest news on the inspection website is clearly not enough to inform citizens about the changed order.
Some could register in a "personal account" to receive a one-time service and have long forgotten about it.
These people will not wait for notifications by mail and, without knowing it, fall into the category of non-payers with all the ensuing consequences.
Access to the "Personal account of the taxpayer" is carried out in three ways: through the account of the portal gosuslugi.ru, using an electronic signature or entering the login and password specified in the registration card.
The latter can be obtained in person at any department of the tax inspection (regardless of the place of registration).
We remind you that this year the transport tax must be paid before December 1.
Notifications began in July.
